======================================================================
  Part 8: TERNARY-ROOT COLUMN = CONVOLUTION OF CATALAN^3
======================================================================

When the ternary node is at the root:
  = sum_{i+j+k=n} C_{i-1} C_{j-1} C_{k-1}
  = 3-fold Catalan convolution!

3-fold Catalan convolution (ternary root contributions):
  n=3, m=n-3=0: conv3=     1, FC(3,0)=     1, C(2m+2,m+1)/(m+2)=     1
